#, fuzzy
msgid "The A2A Java SDK provides the tools to manage asynchronous, long-running processes, which we call Tasks. As described in the https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/key-concepts/[Core Concepts] section of the A2A protocol documentation (as well as the https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/life-of-a-task/[Life of a Task] and https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/streaming-and-async/[Streaming and Asynchronous Operations for Long-Running Tasks] sections), a Task can move through various states."
msgstr "El SDK Java de A2A proporciona las herramientas para gestionar procesos asíncronos de larga duración, a los que llamamos Tareas. Como se describe en la sección link:https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/key-concepts/[Conceptos básicos] de la documentación del protocolo A2A (así como en las secciones link:https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/life-of-a-task/[Vida de una tarea] y link:https://a2a-protocol.org/latest/topics/streaming-and-async/[Operaciones de streaming y asíncronas para tareas de larga duración] ), una tarea puede pasar por varios estados."

#: _posts/2025-10-31-quarkus-a2a-cloud-enhancements.adoc
